() Tj
T* (```text) Tj
T* (The common phrase 'knowledge is power' accurately paints the situation at hand. Through) Tj
T* (censorship in libraries, which are meant to allow free access to all media-related materials, we) Tj
T* (take away the opportunity for people to empower themselves through knowledge. The reasons for) Tj
T* (not censoring media in libraries are numerous and include, but are not limited to,) Tj
T* (unconstitutionality of censorship, the lack of proper definition for 'offensive', and the) Tj
T* (contradiction censorship poses to the core of what a library is. The first, and most blatant,) Tj
T* (reason for not allowing the censorship of materials in libraries is the unconstitutionality of) Tj
T* (the matter. Freedom of speech and freedom of press are both protected by the constitution upon) Tj
T* (which our country was founded. Censorship of said materials will effectively undermine both of) Tj
T* (these rights. Authors, illustrators, journalists and the slew of other individuals who compose) Tj
T* (the materials available in libraries are exercising their right to free speech through their) Tj
T* (works. They are constitutionally protected in the things they say. Notice that @CAPS1 have a) Tj
T* (right to free speech and not a right to free speech so long as no one is offended. The freedom) Tj
T* (of press is the means by which they share their ideas and concepts with the world. They are) Tj
T* (utilizing their free speech by means of press. Censoring library materials would be limiting the) Tj
T* (means by which artists can share their ideas with citizens of the @LOCATION1. This would be a) Tj
T* (clear failure to uphold the rights of the citizens. For this reason, we cannot censor libraries.) Tj
T* (The constitutional concept of equality of man plays into the situation as well. There is no) Tj
T* (adequate legal definition of 'offend'. People could be offended by something as serious as a) Tj
T* (personal attack on their beliefs and personal entity or something as light as a personal) Tj
T* (distaste for certain mindsets and ideas. So, because all men are equal, we would have to respect) Tj
T* (the 'offense' taken by all people and to all degrees. This leaves every single work of art,) Tj
T* (whether it be a book, movie, magazine or any other form provided by libraries, open to the) Tj
T* (fickle definition of offensive and vulnerable to the personal feelings of every individual. If) Tj
T* (said offense taken by individuals to works is able to mark a work as 'offensive' and thus make) Tj
T* (it open to removal from libraries, we are effectively allowing citizens to undermine the rights) Tj
T* (of other citizens. This is something that cannot be allowed in our libraries. The final core) Tj
T* (issue is the essence of censorship versus the essence of a library. Censorship is meant to) Tj
T* (create a politically correct and non-offensive environment through the limitation of exposure to) Tj
T* (materials. Libraries, however, are meant to allow public access to works that stretch and) Tj
T* (challenge knowledge, beliefs, notions and all ideas held by people through the works of others.) Tj
T* (Censorship cannot be implemented without a clash with the essence of a library's purpose. If) Tj
T* (censorship were to be enacted, a library could not provide new information if someone else did) Tj
T* (not like what was being taught. A library could not provide works that challenge and stretch) Tj
T* (individual beliefs if someone was offended by the means by which the stretching occurred. Pre-) Tj
T* (conceived notions could not be defeated with the presence of factual knowledge if someone did) Tj
T* (not like the truth. In all of these ways, and many more, a library's core ideals and purpose) Tj
T* (could not be upheld with the induction of a system of censorship. All in all, we can see that) Tj
T* (censorship could only hope to destroy the system libraries abide by. The constitutional rights) Tj
T* (of citizens would be infringed upon, the fickle nature of humans and the lack of definition for) Tj
T* ('offensive' would allow people to undermine the rights of others, and the essence of what a) Tj
T* (library really is would be ravaged. We cannot, as @CAPS1 with rights, employ a system of) Tj
T* (censorship) Tj
T* (```) Tj
